solution.p:
Think of \cos (t) as a single variable, and multiply by each term inside parentheses. (The algebraic form of the calculation is shown on the right in blue).
        \cos (t)  \Big(3 \cos (t) - 2\Big)\amp = \Big(\cos (t)\Big)\Big(3 \cos (t)\Big) - \Big(\cos (t)\Big)\cdot 2  \amp \amp  \blert{x (3x-2) = x\cdot 3x - x\cdot 2}
            \amp = 3\cos^2 (t) - 2\cos (t) \amp \amp \blert{=3x^2 - 2x}
  Notice that we write \Big(\cos (t)\Big)^2 as \cos^2 (t).
